  "texts": [
    "Conversely, illicit or traditionally stigmatised occupations experience underestimation, compared to human scores.",
    "Moreover, for certain occupations, GPT-4's justifications exhibit a lack of contextual awareness.",
    "Insights provided in the justifications suggest that GPT-4 might place excessive value on formal occupational requirements while undervaluing the crucial social roles attributed by human respondents.",
    "These findings are congruent with prior research that has delved into the examination of stereotypes and biases present in LLMs (e.g., Cheng et al. 2023).",
    "Demographic divisions of the human survey sample reveal further differentials between GPT-4 scores and human respondent groups, with notable age and racial dynamics coming to the fore."
  ],
